This paper involves the analysis of eye movement patterns during face recognition, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the study involves cognitive activities and deception, which could also be relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The use of Hidden Markov models and Gaussian emission suggests a machine learning approach, which could also place this paper in the categories of cryptography (cs.CR) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
